title: Man Utd News: Zlatan Ibrahimovic makes fun of Arsenal trophy drought | Metro News

text:
Metro Sport Reporter for Metro.co.uk Sunday 26 Feb 2017 9:50 pm Zlatan Ibrahimovic scored a late winner to help Manchester United to EFL Cup final success over Southampton (Picture: Getty Images) 
Zlatan Ibrahimovic mocked Arsenal and Liverpool for their lack of major trophies in recent years after Manchester United’s EFL Cup final win over Southampton. Ibrahimovic gives Mourinho's Man Utd reign lift-off with EFL Cup final win 
The 35-year-old scored twice, including the late winner which took his tally to 26 this season, as United edged a five-goal thriller at Wembley on Sunday. 
Including the Community Shield, Ibrahimovic now has two winners’ medals during his seven months in England, half as many trophies as Arsenal have collected since 2005. Ibrahimovic’s 26th goal of the season secured a 3-2 win over Southampton at Wembley (Picture: Getty) 
Liverpool, meanwhile, have only one FA Cup and a League Cup success as tangible reward for their efforts since 2006 and the iconic Swede wasted no time in pointing out those facts after his matchwinning heroics. 
‘We are winning. After seven months I have two trophies with this club,’ said Ibrahimovic, who famously turned down the chance to join Arsenal as a youngster after refusing to take part in a trial.
